prompts.frontCover: minimalist 2D cartoon, a charmingly grumpy slice of birthday cake wearing a tiny, crooked party hat, standing alone on a clean white plate. The slice of cake has simple dot eyes and a slight frown, looking overwhelmed. A single, unlit candle sticks out from the top. Above the cake, in the center of the image, is the phrase "I was told there would be no math" written in a beautiful, elegant, and perfectly readable handwritten cursive script. The entire design is set against a solid, soft pastel background, emphasizing a clean, flat aesthetic with simple shapes and a humorous, lighthearted tone.
